Below is one complete solution. In this version, we attach event handlers to the form so that:

- **Clear:** When the “Clear” (reset) button is clicked, the form fields are explicitly cleared (even though the built‐in reset would normally do this) so that the Create/Update section is fully blank.
- **Create/Update:** When the form is submitted, the handler checks if the provided Bid already exists in the books array. If not, a new book is appended; if it does exist, the corresponding entry is updated. In both cases the books table is re‐rendered via the call to renderBooksTable() and the form is reset afterward.

